{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}} [[File:Delimara Power Station 2009.JPG|thumb|[[Delimara Power Station]]]] [[File:Marsa Power Station 2009.jpg|thumb|[[Marsa Power Station]]]] [[File:Malta - Marsaxlokk - Triq Delimara - Xrobb L-Ghagin 11 ies.jpg|thumb|Wind turbine in Malta]] '''Energy in Malta''' describes [[Energy industry|energy]] production, consumption and import in [[Malta]].
Malta has no domestic resource of fossil fuels and no gas distribution network. Gross consumption has increased by 53% in 1990-2004. In 2008 the [[renewable energy]] market was at an early stage in Malta. Only solar energy and biofuels were used. The potential for [[Solar energy|solar]] and [[Wind power|wind]] is substantial according to the EU.<ref name=fact2008>[http://www.energy.eu/renewables/display.php?chart=factsheets/2008_res_sheet_malta_en.pdf Malta. Renewable Energy Fact Sheet] 23 Jan 2008</ref> Energy import dependency was 100% in 2004.<ref name=fact2007>[http://ec.europa.eu/energy/energy_policy/doc/factsheets/mix/mix_mt_en.pdf MALTA – Energy Mix Fact Sheet] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081002203232/http://ec.europa.eu/energy/energy_policy/doc/factsheets/mix/mix_mt_en.pdf |date=2 October 2008 }} January 2007</ref>
